  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd9\u0db8\u0ddd\u0daf\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dd3 \u0db6\u0dbb\u0db4\u0dad\u0dc5\u0dc0 \u0dbb\u0ddd\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Hit by a train at Demodara and seriously in hospital",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the Ella Police, a person who was hit by a train this afternoon (26) was seriously injured and admitted to the Badulla General Hospital near the historic Skyscraper Arch Bridge between Ella Demodara railway stations.",
        "Police said that the injured person is a 46-year-old resident of Ella Karadagolla area.",
        "The police said that part of the left leg and part of the left arm of the person who was hit by the train were separated from the body.",
        "The police said that he hit the goods train which was running between Badulla and Kandy.",
        "The police said that the injured person was immediately taken to the Badulla General Hospital by a Suvasarya 1990 ambulance on the basis of information provided by a passer-by who saw the seriously injured person lying down with blood near the railway track.",
        "Dr. Palitha Rajapaksa, Senior Medical Officer of Badulla General Hospital, Uva Provincial Coordinator of the Government Medical Officers Association, stated that although the part of the injured person's leg and hand were put in an ice box and taken to the hospital, the leg and the hand were not in a suitable condition for re-transplantation. .",
        "Mr. Rajapaksa further said that the delicate and other blood vessels of the separated parts of the leg and hand were destroyed by being hit by the train. Ella police are conducting further investigations."
      ],
